{"id": 223749814, "title": "Famous women you had no idea served in the military", "text": "Women have been an important part of the armed services since the beginning, with icons like Harriet Tubman participating in the Civil War. While being female in a traditionally male-dominated space hasn't always been easy, these women have stuck it out and served their countries.In 2022, the US Department of Defense reported the percentage of women serving in active and reserve capacities was growing. In 2021, 17.3% of active-duty roles and 21.4% of the National Guard and reserves were women, up slightly from the year before, it reported, citing the 2021 Demographics Profile of the Military Community.Ahead of Memorial Day this year \u2014 the official marker of summer and one of the biggest holidays in the US \u2014 here are 12 famous women who have served in the military around the world, including Bea Arthur, Queen Elizabeth, and more. Melina Glusac contributed to a previous version of this article.", "summary": "Queen Elizabeth was a military truck driver during World War II, while \"Golden Girl\" Bea Arthur was a&nbsp;staff&nbsp;sergeant for&nbsp;the Marines.", "url": "https://www.businessinsider.com/women-served-military-2018-11", "image": "https://i.insider.com/636d16d9f5877200181c45be?width=1136&format=jpeg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 15:57:39", "author": "Gabbi Shaw", "authors": ["Gabbi Shaw"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.528}